WEBVTT

00:00:03.370 --> 00:00:06.160
Buying supplies for the 
athletic festival, huh?

00:00:06.520 --> 00:00:07.980
That takes me back.

00:00:10.410 --> 00:00:13.230
Will I be able to lead everyone well enough?

00:00:13.230 --> 00:00:17.250
Yeah, it is a pretty big mall.

00:00:19.960 --> 00:00:21.990
I'm excited, though.

00:00:22.600 --> 00:00:24.590
Will you have time to catch the bus?

00:00:24.590 --> 00:00:25.240
Plenty.

00:00:25.750 --> 00:00:27.840
Did you check the weekend schedule?

00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:29.580
I'll check it again!

00:00:29.580 --> 00:00:30.950
Whoa, whoa. Hold still.

00:00:30.950 --> 00:00:32.360
R-Right...

00:00:32.360 --> 00:00:34.770
I'll go get the schedule!

00:00:35.050 --> 00:00:37.260
It's on the shelf in the living room.

00:00:40.350 --> 00:00:41.950
There, all done.

00:00:47.300 --> 00:00:48.560
Thanks!

00:02:24.460 --> 00:02:25.900
<i>Next stop...</i>

00:02:26.660 --> 00:02:31.000
<i>Amatsumiko-mae. Amatsumiko-mae.</i>

00:02:33.290 --> 00:02:38.800
Episode Nine 
Ready... Up!

00:03:32.560 --> 00:03:33.190
<b>The End</b>

00:03:33.190 --> 00:03:33.310
<b>The End</b>

00:03:33.310 --> 00:03:33.440
<b>The End</b>

00:03:33.690 --> 00:03:33.810
<b>The End</b>

00:03:33.810 --> 00:03:35.060
<b>The End</b>

00:03:38.770 --> 00:03:40.070
<i>Next stop...</i>

00:03:40.070 --> 00:03:45.060
<i>Sennosawa Mall. Sennosawa Mall.</i>

00:03:48.070 --> 00:03:50.500
Morning, Kojou-san. We're here.

00:03:53.180 --> 00:03:54.380
Sorry.

00:03:54.380 --> 00:03:57.450
That always happens when 
I get too absorbed in a book.

00:03:57.450 --> 00:03:59.340
That's some amazing concentration.

00:04:00.200 --> 00:04:03.010
Thank goodness you were on the same bus.

00:04:03.010 --> 00:04:05.570
I miss my stop all the time.

00:04:05.570 --> 00:04:07.100
Hey!

00:04:07.100 --> 00:04:09.320
Over here!

00:04:09.320 --> 00:04:11.200
Hey!

00:04:11.810 --> 00:04:14.810
Morning, Erika-chan, Usagihara-san!

00:04:14.810 --> 00:04:15.780
Morning.

00:04:15.780 --> 00:04:16.840
Morning.

00:04:17.050 --> 00:04:19.770
Wow, you guys look pretty 
different in regular clothes.

00:04:19.770 --> 00:04:20.870
True.

00:04:21.350 --> 00:04:22.390
Yeah...

00:04:25.430 --> 00:04:27.480
It's kinda embarrassing.

00:04:27.960 --> 00:04:30.300
Nah, you look cute. That getup suits you.

00:04:30.300 --> 00:04:32.020
You look cute, too!

00:04:33.010 --> 00:04:35.160
The braid looks really stylish!

00:04:37.570 --> 00:04:39.570
I put a little effort into it.

00:04:39.570 --> 00:04:41.490
Your nails are cute, too!

00:04:41.490 --> 00:04:42.670
Aren't they?

00:04:42.670 --> 00:04:44.910
They're only for today, though.

00:04:45.200 --> 00:04:47.060
And look at you, Komichi-san.

00:04:47.060 --> 00:04:47.770
Huh?

00:04:47.770 --> 00:04:48.750
Your hair.

00:04:50.360 --> 00:04:51.600
You can tell?

00:04:51.600 --> 00:04:54.370
Yeah. It's a little shorter now.

00:04:57.780 --> 00:05:00.550
Well, ready to go get those supplies?

00:05:02.400 --> 00:05:04.910
The things we need for the 
athletic festival are...

00:05:04.910 --> 00:05:07.060
Vinyl tape for the cheer squad,

00:05:07.060 --> 00:05:08.910
cloth to make the class flags,

00:05:08.910 --> 00:05:11.610
and a few other little things.

00:05:11.610 --> 00:05:13.810
There's a directory over there.

00:05:13.810 --> 00:05:15.060
Leave it to me!

00:05:15.930 --> 00:05:19.070
I'll be your guide to this mall today!

00:05:24.760 --> 00:05:28.260
Wow... It's almost like 
we're at an amusement park.

00:05:28.660 --> 00:05:32.400
I've never shopped at a place like 
this before, so I'm kinda excited.

00:05:32.400 --> 00:05:34.260
It has a movie theater, too.

00:05:34.260 --> 00:05:35.260
Really?

00:05:35.260 --> 00:05:39.480
I've actually never been to 
this particular mall, either.

00:05:39.480 --> 00:05:42.520
Which stores do you usually 
go to, Akebi-san?

00:05:43.870 --> 00:05:45.540
I go to...

00:05:45.530 --> 00:05:47.530
Veggie Fest

00:05:45.790 --> 00:05:47.090
The grocery store!

00:05:47.530 --> 00:05:48.800
This place is huge.

00:05:47.530 --> 00:05:49.740
Seasonal

00:05:47.530 --> 00:05:49.740
Fruits

00:05:47.530 --> 00:05:49.740
<b>Oranges</b>

00:05:47.530 --> 00:05:49.740
<b>Dekopon</b>

00:05:49.740 --> 00:05:51.740
<b>Champon Ken</b>

00:05:50.130 --> 00:05:51.480
The food court!

00:05:51.760 --> 00:05:53.240
They all look so good!

00:05:53.950 --> 00:05:55.950
<b>Play Room</b>

00:05:54.620 --> 00:05:55.960
The play room!

00:05:56.260 --> 00:05:59.950
These mats are super soft. It's really fun!

00:05:59.950 --> 00:06:00.960
There we go!

00:06:00.960 --> 00:06:02.860
Whoa, whoa! Akebi-chan!

00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:06.220
I kind of dressed up for this.

00:06:06.220 --> 00:06:08.760
Oh, right! I guess you 
can't play in that, huh?

00:06:08.760 --> 00:06:09.720
I got too excited...

00:06:10.940 --> 00:06:13.280
I can totally relate, though.

00:06:13.280 --> 00:06:15.050
I have a little brother,

00:06:15.050 --> 00:06:18.040
so I used to play with him in 
these things all the time.

00:06:18.430 --> 00:06:19.930
Exactly!

00:06:21.230 --> 00:06:26.970
Kao and I used to play here while we 
waited for Mom to finish shopping.

00:06:28.290 --> 00:06:32.750
Then Mom would buy us ice cream 
or taiyaki or something,

00:06:32.750 --> 00:06:34.080
and we'd all eat together.

00:06:34.080 --> 00:06:37.240
I guess you have a lot 
of memories here, huh?

00:06:37.240 --> 00:06:37.850
Yeah!

00:06:38.190 --> 00:06:40.150
When my dad had the day off work,

00:06:40.150 --> 00:06:43.160
we'd go play in the river 
after the shopping was done!

00:06:43.160 --> 00:06:44.100
Sounds fun.

00:06:44.100 --> 00:06:44.870
Ooh!

00:06:45.570 --> 00:06:47.990
I didn't know this store 
was at this mall, too!

00:06:48.210 --> 00:06:50.470
I've never been in there...

00:06:50.470 --> 00:06:52.870
They have all kinds of cute accessories.

00:06:52.870 --> 00:06:54.400
Let's take a look!

00:06:56.060 --> 00:06:58.970
<i>Usagihara-san knows more about it than I do!</i>

00:06:58.970 --> 00:07:00.630
Hey, Akebi-chan!

00:07:00.630 --> 00:07:03.740
This is the brand that 
Fukumoto Miki modeled for!

00:07:03.950 --> 00:07:05.110
Miki-chan?!

00:07:06.390 --> 00:07:09.630
Wow! They actually sell these here?

00:07:09.630 --> 00:07:13.000
And it's not that expensive. 
I bet it'd look good on you.

00:07:14.990 --> 00:07:16.460
Yep, it totally does!

00:07:20.980 --> 00:07:22.760
<i>Usagihara-san's amazing!</i>

00:07:22.760 --> 00:07:24.630
Oh, this is cute.

00:07:23.230 --> 00:07:24.880
Hm, nice.

00:07:24.880 --> 00:07:27.460
Oh, they have that brand here, too!

00:07:53.280 --> 00:07:55.730
Wow, they even have this store here!

00:07:55.730 --> 00:07:56.990
Wow...

00:07:56.990 --> 00:07:59.430
Wow, and this store, too!

00:07:59.430 --> 00:08:01.820
<i>Shouldn't we be buying supplies?</i>

00:08:03.500 --> 00:08:05.000
Dragonfly Books

00:08:07.380 --> 00:08:10.670
Oh, I go to that bookstore sometimes, too.

00:08:11.590 --> 00:08:13.420
Oh, really?

00:08:15.710 --> 00:08:17.770
I'd like to check it out, too.

00:08:33.270 --> 00:08:34.750
That book...

00:08:35.520 --> 00:08:37.130
What a coincidence!

00:08:37.580 --> 00:08:42.330
I just finished reading that on my way here.

00:08:42.330 --> 00:08:45.540
I've been curious about this 
author's work for a while.

00:08:45.540 --> 00:08:47.280
Want to borrow my copy?

00:08:48.570 --> 00:08:49.720
Really?

00:08:49.720 --> 00:08:50.610
Sure!

00:08:52.120 --> 00:08:55.640
I'd like to hear your thoughts about 
it when you finish reading it.

00:08:55.640 --> 00:08:56.420
Okay.

00:08:57.540 --> 00:09:00.050
Do you do any writing, Kojou-san?

00:09:00.330 --> 00:09:03.030
The literature club kinda 
gives me that impression.

00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:04.790
That's true.

00:09:04.790 --> 00:09:08.880
There were kids in grade school who liked 
reading books and wrote some of their own.

00:09:08.880 --> 00:09:10.060
Right?

00:09:11.150 --> 00:09:15.270
Actually... I thought I'd 
like to try writing one.

